<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08843</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING COMPASSIONATE AND RIGHT OF ACCESS TO MEDICAL  CANNABIS AND EXPANDING RESEARCH INTO ITS MEDICINAL PROPERTIES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to provide patients and those afflicted with serious diseases to have alternative
option in treating their illness and alleviate their suffering from it by allowing the use
of "medical cannabis" with the proper diagnosis and prescription by licensed physicians.

Intends to provide safety measures and regulation on the medical use of cannabis which has been confirmed to have beneficial and therapeutic uses to treat chronic or debilitating diseases
or medical condition that produces one or more of the following: cachexia or wasting syndrome; severe and chronic pain; severe nausea; seizures (like epilepsy); or severe and persistent muscle spasms (like multiple sclerosis), to ensure the health and safety of the public.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SY-ALVARADO, JOSE ANTONIO &quot;KUYA JONATHAN&quot; R.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-01-16</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2019-01-22</td></tr></table>